        <p MadCap:conditions="">The <strong class="Variable">Heat</strong> will be <span class="Synonym">playing</span> in front of a home crowd <strong class="Variable">Thursday</strong> at the <strong class="Variable">American Airlines Arena</strong> in <strong class="Variable">Miami</strong>. The <strong class="Variable">Heat</strong>, <strong class="Variable">fifth</strong> in the <strong class="Variable">Eastern Conference</strong>, have had a <span class="Synonym">strong</span> season so far, with a <strong class="Variable">5-3</strong> record. On offense, <strong class="Variable">Miami</strong> has been struggling to get points on the scoreboard—only averaging <strong class="Variable">97.1</strong> points per game. <strong class="Variable">Miami </strong>has been averaging <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NBA"><strong class="Variable">36.9</strong> field goals</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NFL"><strong class="Variable">5</strong> touchdowns</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NHL"><strong class="Variable">1.3</strong> goals</MadCap:conditionalText> per game, with just <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NBA"><strong class="Variable">6.9</strong> three-pointers</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NFL"><strong class="Variable">5</strong> field goals</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NHL"><strong class="Variable">2.1</strong> assists</MadCap:conditionalText>. The <strong class="Variable">Miami</strong> defense has lead the league this year. The <strong class="Variable">Heat</strong> have allowed opponents an average of <strong class="Variable">90.1</strong> points per game, picking up <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NBA"><strong class="Variable">7.1</strong> steals</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NFL"><strong class="Variable">3.2</strong> interceptions</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NHL"><strong class="Variable">35</strong> hits</MadCap:conditionalText> and <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NBA"><strong class="Variable">6.9</strong> blocks</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NFL"><strong class="Variable">5.1</strong> sacks</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NHL"><strong class="Variable">27</strong> blocked shots</MadCap:conditionalText> <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NBA,General.NFL">per game</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NHL">overall</MadCap:conditionalText>. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NBA">From the free throw line, the Heat have made <strong class="Variable">77.6</strong> percent of all free throws, averaging <strong class="Variable">16.5</strong> per game</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NFL">Overall, the <strong class="Variable">Heat</strong> offense is averaging <strong class="Variable">361.5</strong> yards per game when they step out on the gridiron</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.NHL">In front of the net, goalie <strong class="Variable">James Reimer</strong> has blocked <strong class="Variable">93.52%</strong> of shots made</MadCap:conditionalText>.</p>
